{% block content %}
  <p class="crumb"><a href="/communities">Communities</a> › <a href="/communities/sagamok">Sagamok Anishnawbek</a> › Questions awaiting an answer</p>

  <h1>Questions awaiting an answer</h1>
  <p class="lead">A growing record of questions members have put to Sagamok Chief and Council, and to the Nation's offices, that are still awaiting a reply. Each entry is tied to a public source or an as-filed document, framed as a question, not an accusation. We post the date asked and the status, and we update it as answers come in. Where there is no reply, that is recorded too. Silence is its own kind of answer.</p>
  <p class="awc-updated">Last updated: July 10, 2026.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-compiled and unofficial.</strong> This is independent and member-led. It is not the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund and is not affiliated with it. It takes no side; it points to what the documents say. Everything here is drawn from the public record. If you can <a href="/about#corrections">show us an inaccuracy</a>, we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  <h2>Open</h2>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>Member records request (16 questions, plus a supplement)</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>June 10, 2026, to Chief and Council through the Council Secretariat.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>How the Nation's settlement capital and enterprise investments are governed and what benefit reaches members, the trust deed and who controls it, the loans to the Nation's companies and their terms, the Finance and Audit Committee's independence, committee memberships, the records-access process, and more. Carried by {{ signatures.total }} signatures ({{ signatures.online }} online and {{ signatures.paper }} on paper), with a written response requested within 30 days.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">No reply</span> &middot; The 30-day response period closed on July 10, 2026 with no records provided and no response received. On July 10 an updated package, the signed request with an evidence appendix grounding each item and an updated list of signatories, was delivered to the full Chief and Council. The request remains open and signatures are still being collected. Read the full request: <a href="/standard/records-request">the records request</a>.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>When is the next Chief and Council meeting, and can members attend?</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>July 3, 2026, to the Council Secretariat and the Political Office.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>The Nation's public website and meeting schedule are out of date, so a member asked three plain questions: when is the next Chief and Council meeting, is it open to members, and how can a member be heard.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">No reply</span> &middot; The public meeting schedule remains out of date, and meeting agendas are not posted, so members cannot readily learn when Council meets or what it is deciding. A member who attended the July 7, 2026 meeting learned the next meeting is July 28, 2026; that date was not available from the posted schedule, which remains out of date.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>The long-term care MOU (Espanola)</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>June 2026, to Chief and Council through the Council Secretariat.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>The June public announcement said Sagamok signed a Memorandum of Understanding with Whitefish River First Nation, the Town of Espanola, and the Espanola Regional Hospital and Health Centre. What did Council authorize, when, and on what terms?</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Partly answered</span> &middot; On July 10, 2026 the signed MOU and two related minutes (December 2, 2025 and May 19, 2026) were posted to the Members Portal. The MOU, dated June 26, 2026, is a non-binding agreement to explore a shared-ownership expansion of the long-term care and assisted living facility in Espanola. What remains unanswered: the two minutes record a 10,000 dollar concept-drawing approval and the motions to enter and exit closed session, but not the resolution that authorized signing the MOU, its terms, or who signed. That authorization has been requested and is still awaited.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>The members-portal disclosure (letter to Chief and Council)</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>June 1, 2026, to the Political Office, delivered to Chief and Council; escalated July 3, 2026.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>A member raised that the members portal had left member information open, asked Council to confirm it was fixed and to account for it. The July 3 follow-up noted that the gated pages and confidential-document passwords have been captured in the public Internet Archive. The exposure has since been resolved (see <a href="/communities/sagamok/members-website-issue">the members website issue</a>); a substantive response from Council to the letter is still outstanding.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Awaiting</span> &middot; Acknowledgement only; awaiting a substantive response.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>The July 20 Elders Forum and day trip</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>June 2026, to the Political Office.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>Which department owns and funds the event (catering, busing, and agenda) and why an elders program is administered through the Political Office rather than a wellness or service department; and what consideration was given to elder financial wellbeing in scheduling a stop at a casino on a band-organized, band-funded elders trip, including who approved it and out of which budget.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Awaiting</span></dd>
      <dt>Source</dt>
      <dd>The Nation's public notice for the Elders Forum, July 20, 2026.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>The full draft of the proposed Community Safety By-law</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>July 8, 2026, to the Political Office and Council Secretariat.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>At the July 7, 2026 Council meeting, Falls Law presented a proposed Community Safety By-law, covering removal powers, trespass notices, appeal rights, enforcement officers, penalties, housing implications, and how the law would apply to members and non-members. A member asked for the full current draft, any plain-language summary or presentation materials shared with Council, the expected member-engagement schedule, and the expected date Council will be asked to consider or approve it, so members can read it before it returns to Council.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Awaiting</span></dd>
      <dt>Source</dt>
      <dd>The July 7, 2026 Chief and Council meeting; written request sent July 8, 2026.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <div class="awc-item">
    <h3>Missing accepted Council minutes and committee records</h3>
    <dl>
      <dt>Asked</dt>
      <dd>July 9, 2026, to the Political Office, Council Secretariat, Governance, and Administration.</dd>
      <dt>What it asks</dt>
      <dd>Several sets of minutes appear to have been accepted or received by Council but are not posted in the public minutes archive. A member asked who is responsible for maintaining the Council minutes archive and the committee minutes archive, whether final accepted records exist for the dates below, when they will be posted, and how members can obtain copies in the meantime: August 26, 2024; March 25, 2025; June 10, 2025; July 22, 2025; August 1, 2025; November 4, 2025; November 11, 2025; and the Finance and Audit Committee's September 30, 2024 and October 7, 2024 meetings.</dd>
      <dt>Status</dt>
      <dd><span class="awc-status">Awaiting</span></dd>
      <dt>Source</dt>
      <dd>Written request sent July 9, 2026.</dd>
    </dl>
  </div>

  <h2>Answered</h2>
  <p class="awc-empty">Nothing here yet. As replies arrive, they move to this section with the date and a short summary of what was provided.</p>

  <h2>How this list works</h2>
  <ul class="awc-how">
    <li>Every item is a question grounded in a public source or an as-filed document, never an accusation about any person.</li>
    <li>An item stays under "Open" until the Nation provides a written answer, then it moves to "Answered" with the date and what was said.</li>
    <li>This is a member resource. If you have asked Council something and are still waiting, or if you think we have a detail wrong, <a href="/about#corrections">tell the Circle</a> and we will record it or correct it.</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="cover__byline">A community resource from the Robinson Huron Treaty hub, member-led and independent. Facts are from public sources; the questions are for our leadership. Corrections welcome.</p>
{% endblock %}
